ike gene and are therefore unlikely to be infective for humans. These results demonstrate a lack, or at least low incidence, of SARS-C\u00ad oV-2\u00ad spill over from humans to susceptible GB bats, and confirm that sarbecovirus infection is widespread in R. hipposideros. Despite frequently sharing roost sites with R. ferrumequinum, no evidence of cross-\u00adspecies transmission was found.", "access_right": "restricted", "creators": [{"name": "Apaa, Ternenge", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Withers, Amy J.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Staley, Ceri", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Blanchard, Adam", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Bennett, Malcolm", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Bremner-Harrison, Samantha", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Chadwick, Elizabeth A.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Hailer, Frank", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Harrison, Stephen W. R.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Loose, Matthew", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Mathews, Fiona", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Tarlinton, Rachael", "affiliation": null}], "keywords": ["Biodiversity", "Mammalia", "Chiroptera", "Chordata", "Animalia", "bats", "bat"], "related_identifiers": [{"identifier": "hash://md5/8913be7907cd469b2a5dffe45c318656", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "hash://sha256/c2321b6bb9ce4dd6dc34388b2f088408a3bc21f49f192e021576cd3fd5c408c1", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "zotero://select/groups/5435545/items/NT3LUHWK", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "https://zotero.org/groups/5435545/items/NT3LUHWK", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "https://linker.bio/cut:hash://md5/43420122a3783887350c513f5ee1521f!/b132887-135345", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "hash://md5/ce1e7618f237ff56e74d51f496e811a3", "relation": "isPartOf", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "10.5281/zenodo.1410543", "relation": "isCompiledBy", "resource_type": "software